5:
I guess we're all done for today!
Thanks for the help, you two!
9:
Thanks for bringing us along! We'll
be eating well tonight!
33: Tsk! I can't stand these pests!
57: This model number... Oh, come on!
60:
I'm sorry, Stella. Some old ghosts are
haunting me.
64:
But don't worry! You're not getting
hurt on my watch!
77:
Shut your stinking mouth and show
yourself.
80:
My, you've become so vulgar. What
ever happened to you?
84: I told you to shut it, bastard.
92:
He's my old boss. The living
embodiment of this city's despair.
Concentrated sludge that talks.
95: Such strong feelings. Eh, no matter.
97:
Let me get to the point. We want you
back, Strina.
103:
You're aware of DayAndNight's
decline, yes? And what's being done
to ensure its demise?
106:
...Don't tell me you're after the head
of Noxel Group!
108:
Finally, an actual reaction. Looks like
my favorite dog might still have
some bite.
110:
Come along now, Strina. Together,
we can bring down anything and
anyone we like.
112:
You're a professional at taking
things apart. Stop pretending to be
some loose-cannon delinquent that
just breaks things for fun.
118:
You don't get to decide who I am!
And you DEFINITELY aren't about to
lead me around on a leash!
133: Well, she'll just get in our way.
137:
Oops. Looks like someone
underestimated me again.
141:
Huh?! What are you brainless
drones doing? MOVE!
144:
You're terrible at finishing a job, you
know that?
147:
Like you said, I take things apart. No
matter how complicated it might
seem...
150:
Do you really think I can't repurpose
machines that I built myself?
Dumbass.
153:
H-how?! You were FUMING! How
could you even think straight, let
alone repurpose—
156:
Oh, I took care of it before you even
showed up. It didn't take much to
figure out what you were doing.
159:
I could have done better, though. I
shouldn't have blown my top like
that.
163:
Thanks, Stella. Your words meant a
lot to me!
167: I am happy to hear that.
170:
W-wait! I'm sorry! I'll give you an
incredible wage and benefits!
Anything you want, just—
173: Anything I want, eh? In that case...
184:
Ahahaha! Did you see the way he
was pissing his pants?
187:
I made him totally eat it! We even
got that pig behind bars!
190:
Trash like him only know how to talk
big and stroke their egos!
194:
You, uh... got some pent-up
frustration, huh...
198:
...I'm sorry, you two. I shouldn't have
gotten you caught up in my
problems.
201:
Not at all. Thanks for keeping Stella
safe.
205:
Stella was the one who helped me,
actually.
215:
When I'm with you, I feel like there's
nothing I can't do. So I'm sure I'll be a
big help around here!
218:
I'm looking forward to a bright future
with you all!
223: We're happy to have you with us.
228:
We sure are. We'll be relying on you
a lot.
